criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patient diagnosed with a solitary benign or malignant neoplasm localized in the right
             colon

          -  Patients aged 18 years or older

          -  Patients who give written informed consent

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  acute intestinal obstruction

          -  colon perforation;

          -  liver and/or lung metastases;

          -  multiple primary colonic tumors;

          -  scheduled need for synchronous intra-abdominal surgery;

          -  preoperative evidence of invasion of adjacent structures, as assessed by CT or
             ultrasonography;

          -  previous ipsilateral colon surgery.
